**दुष्टउ शरण आनि जब परई । पूरण इच्छा उनकी करई ॥**

Word-by-word breakdown:

**दुष्टउ** (dushta-u) - "even the wicked" or "even evil ones"
**शरण** (sharana) - "refuge" or "shelter"
**आनि** (ani) - "coming" or "taking"
**जब** (jaba) - "when"
**परई** (parai) - "fall" or "come"

**पूरण** (purana) - "fulfill" or "complete"
**इच्छा** (icchha) - "desire" or "wish"
**उनकी** (unaki) - "their"
**करई** (karai) - "do" or "fulfill"

Translation: "When even wicked people come and take refuge in you, you fulfill their desires."